OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a cold, frosty start, a
OL,6,Ffine day follows with plenty of bright
OL,7,For sunny spells. Dry overall, though a
OL,8,Fslight chance of an isolated coastal
OL,9,Fshower. Feeling cool, particularly
OL,10,Falong coasts in northeasterly winds.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FSunny spells persist through
OL,13,Fthe evening. Temperatures fall quickly
OL,14,Fovernight with a rural frost possible.
OL,15,FCloud thickens later, allowing some
OL,16,Frecovery in temperatures and bringing
OL,17,Fsporadic light rain.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,165,160,301,260,100,100
